org.apache.flink.graph.types.valuearray

接口 ValueArray<T>

  • 类型参数:
    T - the Value type
    所有超级接口:
    java.lang.Comparable<ValueArray<T>>, CopyableValue<ValueArray<T>>, IOReadableWritable, java.lang.Iterable<T>, Key<ValueArray<T>>, NormalizableKey<ValueArray<T>>, ResettableValue<ValueArray<T>>, java.io.Serializable, Value
    所有已知实现类:
    ByteValueArray, CharValueArray, DoubleValueArray, FloatValueArray, IntValueArray, LongValueArray, NullValueArray, ShortValueArray, StringValueArray

    @TypeInfo(value=ValueArrayTypeInfoFactory.class)
public interface ValueArray<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>, IOReadableWritable, java.io.Serializable, NormalizableKey<ValueArray<T>>, ResettableValue<ValueArray<T>>, CopyableValue<ValueArray<T>>
    Basic interface for array types which reuse objects during serialization.

    Value arrays are usable as grouping keys but not sorting keys.

    • 方法详细资料

      • size

        int size()
        Returns the number of elements stored in the array.
        返回:
        the number of elements stored in the array

      • isFull

        boolean isFull()
        An bounded array fills when the allocated capacity has been fully used. An unbounded array will only fill when the underlying data structure has reached capacity, for example the ~2^31 element limit for Java arrays.
        返回:
        whether the array is full

      • add

        boolean add(T value)
        Appends the value to this array if and only if the array capacity would not be exceeded.
        参数:
        value - the value to add to this array
        返回:
        whether the value was added to the array

      • addAll

        boolean addAll(ValueArray<T> source)
        Appends all of the values in the specified array to the end of this array. If the combined array would exceed capacity then no values are appended.
        参数:
        source - array containing values to be added to this array
        返回:
        whether the values were added to the array

      • mark

        void mark()
        Saves the array index, which can be restored by calling reset().

        This is not serialized and is not part of the contract for Key.equals(Object).

      • reset

        void reset()
        Restores the array index to when mark() was last called.

      • clear

        void clear()
        Resets the array to the empty state. The implementation is *not* expected to release the underlying data structure. This allows the array to be reused with minimal impact on the garbage collector.

        This may reset the mark() in order to allow arrays be shrunk.
